<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="408" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[178,1085,283,705]" pageId="19" pageNumber="408">
Diagnosis: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cameron" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[383,606,480,501]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Ferreola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purpureopruinosa">
<emphasis box="[383,606,480,501]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="408">F. purpureopruinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by colour pattern (head, pronotum, mesoscutum, and scutellum red, remaining body black with distinct blue shimmer) in combination with a long malar space (half as long as POL), and a smoth and finely grainlike sculptured propodeal declivitiy with distinct blue shimmer. Propodeal declivity is below separated by prominent edge from propodeal dorsum. Examined female measure 
<quantity box="[353,432,619,640]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="19" pageNumber="408" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
, males 
<quantity box="[517,617,619,640]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="408" unit="mm" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8-10 mm</quantity>
. The males have face partly black, and the propodeal transverse egde carry a dense row of long and fine yellow setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
